        "client_msg_id": "f47b2c8d-af00-4586-8c08-3302fa6a3509",
        "text": "Yeah, I think a big part of what makes the discussion so wacky is that there's an inherent all or nothing assumption that all sides end up making. The HN comments assume that a foundation wouldn't have _more_ things on top, it's somehow solely the commitment system, which is uselessly reductionist. Foundations are for building on and I have no doubt that much of what you'd build on top would be evolutions of things we have today. It's not like law or government or organizations would no longer exist. :stuck_out_tongue: They'd just probably look different and have a different purpose if you changed that piece of the puzzle.",
